metadata.name: serenity
metadata.description:
mount tamalpais
marin county, ca

The perfect storm of serenity. This photo is the rare product of marine fog rolling eastward and a sunset lit by high altitude clouds. 

Hot air rises away from the city of San Francisco, and the rising air mass creates a low-pressure zone. This zone sucks in cold, moist air from the Pacific Ocean, which brings moisture into the local climate. As the air cools below the dew point, fog condenses.
